Here are proficiency-related points for Technology Applications in your role as a Web Developer working with Java, Angular, Spring Boot, OpenShift, and an in-house pipeline:

Proficiency in Technology Applications
	1.	Scalable & High-Performance Architecture – Designs applications with a scalable, cloud-native approach, leveraging microservices, containerization, and efficient data processing.
	2.	Modern Web Development Best Practices – Develops interactive and responsive front-end applications using Angular while ensuring optimal performance and accessibility.
	3.	Efficient Backend Development – Implements well-structured APIs and backend logic in Spring Boot, ensuring security, performance, and maintainability.
	4.	CI/CD & Deployment Automation – Integrates applications with an in-house CI/CD pipeline, automating builds, testing, and deployments for efficient release cycles.
	5.	Security & Compliance – Implements secure authentication, access controls, encryption, and best practices to protect applications from vulnerabilities and ensure compliance with security standards.
	6.	Observability & Monitoring – Incorporates centralized logging (ELK, OpenTelemetry) and monitoring tools (Prometheus, Grafana) to provide real-time application health insights.
	7.	Cloud-Native & Infrastructure Awareness – Ensures applications are optimized for OpenShift deployments, using Kubernetes configurations and Helm charts for efficient resource management.
	8.	Data Management & Optimization – Designs applications with efficient data storage, indexing, and retrieval mechanisms, ensuring scalability and minimal latency.
	9.	Cross-Team Collaboration & Inner Source Contributions – Works in an Inner Source model, sharing reusable components and collaborating across teams to enhance application development.
	10.	Continuous Improvement & Emerging Tech Adoption – Stays updated with the latest advancements in frameworks, cloud technologies, and security practices to enhance application performance and reliability.

Would you like to emphasize specific aspects based on the technology focus of your applications?
